  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>and peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate your <strong>ginger</strong>, then cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Add your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> diced shallot</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661880385990-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661880385990-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661880385990-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661880385990-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661880385990-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>grated ginger </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Using clean hands, knead the <strong>pork mixture</strong> thoroughly until fully combined, then add it<strong> </strong>to one side of a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and shape into a loaf[ves]</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661880392011-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661880392011-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661880392011-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661880392011-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661880392011-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to the potatoes and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a good grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and give them a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661880399989-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661880399989-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661880399989-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661880399989-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661880399989-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 35-40 min or until the meatloaf[ves] is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are crispy</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>hoisin glaze</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661880409804-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661880409804-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661880409804-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661880409804-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661880409804-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meatloaf[ves] is cooked through, pour <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>hoisin glaze </strong>over the top (save the rest for later!) and sprinkle over your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 5 min or until golden and sticky – this is your <strong>hoisin-glazed meatloaf</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661880415749-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661880415749-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661880415749-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661880415749-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661880415749-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While everything's in the oven, wash your <strong>pak choi</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the roots off your <strong>pak choi</strong> and discard, then chop the<strong> white base</strong> into bite-sized pieces (keep the leaves whole!)</p><p>Peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Once everything is almost done, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1661880419908-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1661880419908-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1661880419908-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1661880419908-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1661880419908-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pak choi base</strong>, <strong>pak choi leaves</strong>, <strong>carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the pan with the<strong> remaining chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> grated ginger </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and cook for 2 min – this is your <strong>stir-fried veg</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> remaining hoisin glaze</strong> to a pot with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and gently heat to warm through (alternatively, pop the gravy in the microwave for 1 min to warm through!) – this is your <strong>hoisin gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1661880433770-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1661880433770-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1661880433770-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1661880433770-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1661880433770-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>hoisin-glazed meatloaf </strong>finely<strong> </strong>and serve with the <strong>crispy potatoes </strong>and <strong>stir-fried veg</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>hoisin gravy</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
